<h1 id="abstract-cn">中文摘要</h1>
<p>随着我国对外开放水平不断提高和企业国际化进程持续推进，跨境贸易、海外投资、涉外民商事纠纷等活动日益频繁，涉外法律知识查询与案例分析需求不断增长。然而，现有涉外法律案例资源分布较为分散，不同国家和地区的司法案例通常存储于各自独立的官方网站或法律数据库中，存在检索入口不统一、语言理解门槛高、判决文书篇幅较长、专业术语复杂等问题。传统法律检索系统多以关键词匹配和静态列表展示为主，难以满足用户对案例快速理解、重点提炼和交互式问答的需求。针对上述问题，本文设计并实现了一套涉外法律知识查询与问答系统，旨在为中文用户提供多法域法律案例检索、案例阅读、智能摘要和问答分析等综合服务。</p>
<p>系统采用前后端分离架构进行设计。前端基于 Vue 3 和 Element Plus 构建用户交互界面，提供用户登录注册、案例检索、案例阅读、收藏历史、本地知识库和配额充值等功能页面；后端基于 Spring Boot 框架实现业务逻辑处理，使用 MyBatis 完成数据持久化，使用 MySQL 存储用户信息、案例元数据、案例详情、收藏记录和订单数据等结构化信息，使用 Redis 实现检索结果缓存、验证码存储、分布式锁和摘要配额控制。系统面向美国、日本、欧盟等涉外案例来源，结合爬虫接口与内置桥接机制实现案例数据采集，并通过统一接口对前端提供检索服务。在智能化处理方面，系统接入大语言模型能力，实现关键词抽取、案例摘要生成和基于案例上下文的问答功能；同时构建本地知识库模块，通过文本切片和向量检索机制支持知识入库与问答查询，提高系统对法律文本的组织和利用能力。</p>
<p>在系统实现过程中，本文重点设计了多数据源案例检索流程、异步摘要生成流程、摘要配额扣减与异常退款机制、原文代理与缓存机制、本地知识库检索流程以及前后端接口交互机制。为验证系统的可用性与稳定性，本文从功能测试和非功能测试两个方面进行测试设计，覆盖用户认证、案例检索、案例阅读、AI 摘要、智能问答、收藏历史、知识库问答和支付配额等核心功能，并对响应时间、异常输入、外部服务不可用和缓存效果等非功能指标进行分析。测试结果表明，系统能够较好地完成涉外法律案例的查询、展示、摘要和问答任务，能够在一定程度上降低用户理解涉外判决文书的难度，为涉外法律知识获取和案例分析提供辅助支持。</p>
<p><b>关键词：</b>涉外法律；案例检索；大语言模型；智能问答；知识库</p>

<h1 class="en" id="abstract-en">Abstract</h1>
<p class="en">With the continuous improvement of China's opening-up and the acceleration of enterprise internationalization, cross-border trade, overseas investment, and foreign-related civil and commercial disputes have become increasingly frequent. As a result, the demand for foreign-related legal knowledge inquiry and case analysis has grown significantly. However, existing foreign-related legal case resources are usually distributed across independent official websites or legal databases in different jurisdictions. Users often face problems such as scattered information sources, inconsistent retrieval entrances, language barriers, lengthy judgments, and complex legal terminology. Traditional legal retrieval systems mainly rely on keyword matching and static result presentation, which makes it difficult to meet users' needs for rapid case understanding, key information extraction, and interactive question answering. To address these problems, this thesis designs and implements a foreign-related legal knowledge inquiry and Q&amp;A system, aiming to provide Chinese users with integrated services including multi-jurisdiction case retrieval, case reading, intelligent summarization, and question answering.</p>
<p class="en">The system adopts a front-end and back-end separated architecture. The front end is developed based on Vue 3 and Element Plus, providing pages for user login and registration, case retrieval, case reading, favorites and browsing history, local knowledge base, and quota recharge. The back end is implemented with Spring Boot, while MyBatis is used for data persistence. MySQL stores structured data such as user information, case metadata, case details, favorite records, browsing history, and payment orders. Redis is used for search result caching, verification code storage, distributed locking, and summary quota control. The system collects legal case data from sources related to the United States, Japan, and the European Union through crawler interfaces and built-in bridge mechanisms, and provides unified retrieval services to the front end. In terms of intelligent processing, the system integrates large language model capabilities to support keyword extraction, case summary generation, and context-based case question answering. In addition, a local knowledge base module is designed with text chunking and vector retrieval mechanisms to support knowledge ingestion and question answering, thereby improving the organization and utilization of legal texts.</p>
<p class="en">During the implementation of the system, this thesis focuses on the design of multi-source case retrieval, asynchronous summary generation, summary quota deduction and refund on failure, original document proxy and caching, local knowledge base retrieval, and front-end/back-end API interaction. To verify the usability and stability of the system, both functional and non-functional tests are designed. The functional tests cover user authentication, case retrieval, case reading, AI-based summarization, intelligent question answering, favorites and browsing history, knowledge base Q&amp;A, and payment quota management. The non-functional tests analyze response time, abnormal input handling, external service unavailability, and caching effects. The test results show that the system can effectively support foreign-related legal case inquiry, presentation, summarization, and question answering, reducing the difficulty for users to understand foreign legal judgments and providing auxiliary support for foreign-related legal knowledge acquisition and case analysis.</p>
<p class="en"><b>Key words:</b> foreign-related law; case retrieval; large language model; intelligent question answering; knowledge base</p>

